'''晴空亂流'''（又稱'''晴空湍流'''）簡稱'''CAT ( Clear Air Turbulence)'''，是[[晴天|晴空]]中無法直接以[[肉眼|肉眼]]或光學儀器看到的[[亂流|亂流]]，是因為不同速度的氣團相遇而造成<ref>Stull, B. R., 1988 An introduction to Boundary Layer Meteorology, Kluwert Academic Publishers 666 pp.</ref>，晴空亂流多半沒有[[雲|雲]]。

最可能造成晴空亂流的區域是在[[对流层|对流层]]較高處，約在海拔7000至12000公尺的高度，大約接近[[對流層頂|對流層頂]]。在有[[高速氣流|高速氣流]]的區域常會出現晴空亂流，在較低海拔，靠近山的區域也容易出現。若有出現[[卷云|卷云]]，其造成晴空亂流的機率也很高。

晴空亂流會使飛機乘客乘坐時不適，偶爾會影響飛航安全。晴空亂流的頻率已有增加，推測可能是[[全球暖化效應|全球暖化效應]]。在《[[自然氣候變化|自然氣候變化]]》期刊中，[[雷丁大学|雷丁大学]]的保羅·威廉斯（Paul William）及[[东英吉利亚大学|东英吉利亚大学]]的Manoj Joshi提出了若大氣中的[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]是[[工業革命|工業革命]]前的二倍，中等到強烈的晴空亂流會較現在增加40%至170%<ref>{{doi|10.1038/nclimate1866}}</ref><ref>[http://www.sciencenews.org/view/generic/id/349476/description/News_in_Brief_Rising_carbon_dioxide_means_more_air_turbulence ''Rising carbon dioxide means more air turbulence''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sciencenews.org/view/generic/id/349476/description/News_in_Brief_Rising_carbon_dioxide_means_more_air_turbulence |date=20130831062842 }} April 8, 2013 Vol.183 #9 Science News</ref><ref>[http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2013/04/08/176598063/climate-change-could-equal-teeth-rattling-flights ''Climate Change Could Equal Teeth-Rattling Flights''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2013/04/08/176598063/climate-change-could-equal-teeth-rattling-flights |date=20141113090803 }} April 08, 2013 NPR</ref><ref>[http://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode.cfm?id=warming-planet-means-bumpier-flight-13-04-08 ''Warming Planet Means Bumpier Flights''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.scientificamerican.com/podcast/episode.cfm?id=warming-planet-means-bumpier-flight-13-04-08 |date=20131103181338 }}; "Climate models and turbulence algorithms forecast that, by mid-century, clear-air turbulence will be more violent and transatlantic flights will hit it twice as often"  April 8, 2013 Scientific American</ref><ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-22063340 ''Transatlantic flights 'to get more turbulent''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-22063340 |date=20190405202130 }} 8 April 2013 BBC</ref>。
